    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense faces a challenging slate today, dominated by high-end pitching matchups that necessitate a precise, efficiency-focused approach. The premier play for the lineup is **Jackson Merrill**, who boasts an elite 75.10 score against Feltner. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a rare alignment of a favorable hitter\u2019s park, a soft SP matchup with a 4.63 xERA, and his dynamic platoon advantage. Similarly, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** provides high-floor production at 71.34; his position in the #2 spot and a favorable dynamic platoon advantage against Ritchie make him our most reliable secondary engine. We are also looking for **Drake Baldwin** to capitalize on his #2 order placement against Cavalli, as his 61.45 rating highlights a strong overall profile that warrants a locked-in start.\n\nWe are forced to navigate significant headwinds with our outfield corps, as **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, and **Kyle Tucker** all face elite arms in Joe Ryan and Logan Webb. While **Kyle Tucker** maintains a respectable 51.92 score thanks to a robust xwOBA, the combination of low park factors and high-skill opposing pitching has compressed the ceiling for this group. The most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 41.26 score. While his base projection was solid, the optimizer favored the platoon-neutral efficiency of **Heliot Ramos** and the structural requirements of our infield slots. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given that several hitters, including **Miguel Vargas**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Marcell Ozuna**, are currently listed as \"Lineup Pending.\" We are keeping a close watch on **Marcell Ozuna**, whose matchup against a pitcher of deGrom\u2019s caliber is daunting; should his spot in the batting order shift downward, his already marginal 44.24 score could drop further. Owners should monitor the status of **Jordan Westburg** on the IL and ensure all active roster spots are maximized, particularly as we look to preserve our precious game caps against this tough rotation of opposing hurlers.",
